        "creation_date": 1449505914,
        "body": "<p>(I'm assuming that these nodes/elements all have the same parent document, if not let me know.)  I would get the parent node of that NodeList (entryDataItem) and use <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/org/w3c/dom/Node.html#appendChild%28org.w3c.dom.Node%29\" rel=\"nofollow\">appendChild:<\/a><\/p>\n\n<pre><code>parentOfEntryDataItem.appendChild(node);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>You might have to cast node as a node, not an element.  If you later need that NodeList, you can just say:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>NodeList x = entryDataItem.getChildNodes();\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
